User Management 
.encompasses the creation, modification, and deletion of user accounts 
.controlling their access privileges to databases and objects within the MySQL server 
    .create user
        .creates new user accounts that can access MySQL DB server 
        .allows DB admins to define login credentials and control who can connect to the DB 
    .delete user
    .show user
    .change user password 


MySQL server control:
    .helps manage DB services 
    .controls server availability
    .supports maintenance and troubleshooting 

Connecting to MySQL using CLI:
Prerequisites:
    .MySQL is running 
    .correct username and password
    .know the host (localhost) and port (3306)


Working with DBs on the command line:
.essential operations:
    .DB management - create, select, modify, delete
    .table management - create, alter, drop
    .data manipulation - insert, update, delete, query 

Core DB-level commands 
    .create DB
    .use - selects the activeDB for subsquent commands
    .alter DB - modifies DB attributes 
    .drop DB - deletes DB entirely 
    